cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a deep learning network for binary image recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The network is learning-free, which suggests it may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of moments kernels and binary hashing may also make it relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper involves image processing and feature extraction, which may make it relevant to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed network on a binary image database, which suggests it may also be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
